section.p:

  \boxed{(A\mathbf x)_i = \sum_{j=1}^n a_{ij}x_j}
  \boxed{(AB)_{ij} = \sum_k a_{ik}b_{kj}}
  \boxed{(AB)^T=B^T A^T}
  \boxed{\det \begin{pmatrix} a\amp b\\ c\amp d \end{pmatrix} = ad-bc}
  \boxed{\det(AB)=\det(A)\det(B)}
  \boxed{A^{-1} = \frac{1}{ad-bc} \begin{pmatrix} d\amp -b\\ -c\amp a \end{pmatrix}}

for

  A= \begin{pmatrix} a\amp b\\ c\amp d \end{pmatrix}, \qquad ad-bc\ne0.


  \boxed{A\text{ invertible} \Longleftrightarrow \det A\ne0}
  \boxed{A\mathbf v=\lambda\mathbf v}
  \boxed{\det(A-\lambda I)=0}
  \boxed{A=PDP^{-1}}

when A has enough independent eigenvectors.
